title.narrative: CAPACITY DEV ON EARLY DETECTION&INTERVEN

description.narrative: Primary health care providers have increased knowledge and skills related to child health, nutrition and development, including on early detection and intervention for CWD, which contributes to Child Health, Health Systems Strengthening, Maternal And Newborn Health, Micronutrients, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2020, an increased number of young girls and boys, including Roma and children with disabilities, access and benefit from quality, integrated and inclusive health care
